      <img src="/static14/politics/2026/05/19/npr-swing-voters-trump-president-approval-2026-midterms.webp" alt="These men voted for President Trump. They have very different views of how he's doing" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">These men voted for President Trump. They have very different views of how he's doing</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Two Black men from Georgia who voted for President Trump in 2024 have very different views of how the country is doing now, in the first installment of Swing Shift from NPR's Tamara Keith.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2026/05/19/npr-swing-voters-trump-president-approval-2026-midterms/"  >(Tamara Keith, MPR News)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 21 May 2026 22:28:43 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 21 May 2026 22:28:43 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Hannah Yang, MPR News">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/politics/2026/05/21/mn-counties-await-90-million-dollars-for-upgrading-old-tech-administer-snap-medicaid.webp" alt="Lawmakers approve $90 million for county tech upgrades" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Lawmakers approve $90 million for county tech upgrades</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Workers expect this will eventually speed up the enrollment process for safety net programs and help relieve the pressure they’re under to comply with new federal requirements.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2026/05/21/mn-counties-await-90-million-dollars-for-upgrading-old-tech-administer-snap-medicaid/"  >(Hannah Yang, MPR News)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
</div><div class="column vcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Fri, 22 May 2026 21:05:41 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Fri, 22 May 2026 21:05:41 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Fox News">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/politics/2026/05/22/republicans-get-aggressive-fight-win-top-cop-spots-battleground-states.webp" alt="Republicans get 'aggressive' in fight to win top cop spots in battleground states" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Republicans get 'aggressive' in fight to win top cop spots in battleground states</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      GOP attorneys general groups invest $11 million in TV ads across key battleground states, betting public safety and crime will define 2026 midterm races.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2026/05/22/republicans-get-aggressive-fight-win-top-cop-spots-battleground-states/"  >(Fox News)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
</div></div></fieldset></main>
